text.text: I'm so glad we visited! My daughter and I had such a great time with all the sweet kitties! All the staff are so incredibly nice too! We enjoyed our adorable cookies and cake pops. The little shop has lots of fun, adorable cat themed things too! It was definitely worth the hour drive from our house!

We traveled from Atlanta to come check this place out and we had a great time! The place is clean & there‚Äôs a lot of cool architecture for the cats which is awesome. They seemed well taken care of and happy! The staff were super friendly and the cafe was nice if you want a snack (or to buy a snack for the cats!). I can‚Äôt believe this spot doesn‚Äôt have more reviews‚Äî they‚Äôre doing a really great thing and you should stop by in support! (P.S. we loved Harvey ‚ù§Ô∏è)

My boyfriend took me here for Valentine‚Äôs day and we absolutely loved it!! They dressed up the cats in ties and pearls for the occasion! We also got cheesecake and champagne which were delightful. We will be coming back!

cafes.name: The Catfe
cafes.address: 426 Bethesda School Rd, Lawrenceville, GA 30044, USA

text.text: Very nice cat cafe! The food here is also really good and they have awesome prices. Cinnamon was the sweetest kitty. this place would be a million times better if u guys had like 10 more cats lol üòÇ

My mom, my kids and I visited this wonderful Catfe. First of all, the food is delicious. The drinks are made to order and the gentleman taking our order was super sweet. Secondly, the cats are lovely. There was one called Cinnamon who is a sweet cuddle bug. We saw two other large cats who were very beautiful. Also, the library had so many wonderful books. I highly recommend this place to whoever needs a little break in their day to enjoy delicious food, a lovely drink, and the company of adorable cats.
Super kind staff, cute and cuddly kitties, adorable cat art, and even a cat themed menu. Cannot recommend the catfe enough! I'll definitely be returning:)

I can't say enough about Paws Awhile Cat Cafe. We didn't order any food, but when we checked in, the owner was SO KIND. The little gift shop area has so many options and they are all cat themed. We didn't have a reservation, but they had availability to purchase the 30 min visit we had hoped for. There are a lot of beautiful cats and the place was very clean. There are no cat odors and a very impressive family-friendly area. The concept of this location is heartwarming. From what I understand, the cats ( some or all?) come from Paws Middle Georgia, and the dedication of the volunteers makes me proud to have adopted from them. I could go on and on but moral of my review...THIS PLACE IS a MUST SEE üòÜüòÅü•∞ü•∞ü•∞ We also met some very kind cat lovers during our visit as well

Love a cat cafe!! Didn't get any food, but I believe that had little cafe snacks and drinks. I just went for the cats and planned to eat a big meal afterwards. The decor was amazing and they had plenty of activities and enrichment for the cats. There was an abundance of toys and plenty of places to sit! My favorite were the window hammocks!
I cannot wait to go back during an evening session with adults only. The group of four children that were there were feral. They ran the whole time, scaring most of the cats into hiding. They were picking the cats up and not putting them down when the cats wanted. I had to ask one kid to not put the laser pointer on me. These children  were not unsupervised, they had adults with them. I believe the age is 7 and up and I don't think all the kids were that old.
Overall, I'm very excited to go back and love on some adoptable cats and kittens in a calmer environment.

PERFECT spot for a quick lunch business meeting! Even the kitties were professional and had great input.

The staff is friendly and very helpful. You can tell that she is knowledgeable about cat care and that she cares for them.

The food is in a separate area from where the cats are so if you just want to enjoy a brownie (highly recommend) while you watch the cats through a window you can.

You can‚Äôt talk about the cafe without talking about the cats! If I could take on more pets the ones on the top of my list are Manon and Sir Meow Meow. I was so focused on loving on them I didn‚Äôt get pictures. I am coming back very soon.

Tips: if a bunch of cats surrounding you is not your thing, don‚Äôt sit in the floor. Make sure you wash your hands before for the safety of the kitties! Get there early because if you‚Äôre a first timer you need to sign a waiver and everything. If you get distracted easy maybe don‚Äôt set an hour long meeting, make it longer. You can have the second half of it in the cafe area.

cafes.name: Pounce Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 404 W Broughton St, Savannah, GA 31401, USA

text.text: I loved my visit at Pounce! The cats were so sweet and relaxed. They‚Äôre very well taken care of! Everything was so clean and the service was amazing. I had a meowmosa and I loved it. I wish I could‚Äôve taken Shogun home with me, he was a sweetheart. I hope he finds a loving family soon!

I‚Äôm not a cat person but this place was great. It‚Äôs a very calm and relaxing atmosphere. There are apparently people who come here for weekly therapy, which makes sense. The best part about it is the cats are adoptable. The store has adopted out so many cats over the years that they emptied out the Humane Society in the city and have to import their cats from the next nearby city‚Äôs Humane Society. This place helps humans and cats.

I didn‚Äôt get any food, but they do offer a few options. The staff is great- both with service and keeping the place clean. The environment is always spotless and never smells like it hosts 10+ cats daily. Candy Corn and Demeter were my favorites and I hope they get adopted soon!

Loved my experience here! The store clerk was friendly and very personable. They had recently ‚Äúemployed‚Äù a storefront cat‚Äîa regularly visiting stray‚Äîwhen I visited.

There were adult cats and kittens a plenty! Lots of toys and spaces to use for interacting. Ample space to sit and chill or pet the babies. The space was really clean as well.

The fee is reasonable for an hour AND includes a coffee / tea that you can prepare for yourself.

I will definitely visit again when I‚Äôm in the area!

Staff very informative and helpful. She took care of the place and the cats. We ended up adopting a very cute loving playful kittey named Odette that we renamed Olivia. The setting was different than just an animal shelter. In a shelter they are all in cages. At this place they are all roaming free inside the house (designated room). You pay a small hourly fee to play and chill with all the cats there. Staff was top notch! Thank you Cat Cafe!

This is the cutest place! You can go and play with so many cats!  The adoption fee is very reasonable too, no matter if you're adopting a kitten or an older cat.  We got a new kitten for our family and he's the best!

cafes.name: The Frisky Whisker (Whisker Lounge Cat Research and Therapy Center)
cafes.address: 94 Pryor St SW, Atlanta, GA 30303, USA

text.text: It was an absolute pleasure to stop at this lounge  and spend time with all the cats. Each one was relaxed and loved being petted. The atmosphere was unique, with a cozy music area at the front and a peaceful kitty room in the back. I thoroughly enjoyed the entire experience and would definitely visit again."

Stopped in during a weekend trip and so glad I did, this lounge is clean and inviting and the cats are friendly. The staff were also helpful and obviously cared for the cats. The cat room has no smell or dust like can be found at other cat cafes. There are comfortable places to sit and the cats are soft and well-groomed.

such an adorable little place - i LOVE the decorations and atmosphere! the environment is just lovely. the cats are clearly loved by the employees, and while not the most friendly cuddly kitties ever, they were not mean at all. a few came and sat in my lap on their own accord! these little guys love to play too, with toys and with each other. the employees were very kind and engaged in conversation, making me feel welcome in the space. overall a wonderful experience and i will be going back. and only ten dollars for an unlimited time! was so pleasantly surprised by that
